 Value:** Initializes all fields with null/false/0 defaults and empty function stubs.\n\n**Provider State (useState hooks):**\n- `currentRound: Round | null`\n- `completedRound: Round | null`\n- `recentCandles: Candle[]`\n- `currentPrice: number`\n- `candleProgress: number`\n- `carryoverJackpot: number`\n- `userHistory: UserRoundHistory[]`\n- `pendingAmount: number` (default: DEFAULT_BET_AMOUNT)\n- `pendingSide: BetSide | null`\n- `loading: boolean`\n- `placingBet: boolean`\n- `claiming: boolean`\n\n**Computed Values (useMemo):**\n- `userBet`: Finds user's bet in `currentRound.pool.greenBets` or `.redBets` by address\n- `potentialPayout`: Calculated from user's bet or pending selection using `calculatePotentialPayout()`\n- `userOdds`: User's share of winning pool as percentage\n\n**Key Actions:**\n- `placeBet(sideOverride?)`: Takes optional side override, validates min/max amounts, checks balance, calls `mockPlaceBet()`\n- `adjustBetAmount(\"half\" | \"double\" | \"max\")`: Adjusts pending amount with min/max clamping\n- `refreshRound()`: Updates `currentRound` and `recentCandles` from mock\n- `claimPayout()`: Validates winner status, simulates 1s delay, clears `completedRound`\n- `clearCompletedRound()`: Resets `completedRound` state\n\n**Subscriptions & Polling:**\n- Subscribes to `subscribeToRound()` for round updates\n- Subscribes to `subscribeToCompletedRound()` for result display\n- Polls every 100ms to update `candleProgress` and interpolate `currentPrice`\n- Price interpolation uses bullish/bearish logic based on open vs close\n\n**History Update:** Watches `address` and `currentRound.phase` to fetch and sort user history\n\n---\n\n## File 3: On-Chain State (`sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/closecall/src/state.rs`)\n\n**Rust Enums (all derive AnchorSerialize, AnchorDeserialize, Clone, Copy, Debug, InitSpace):**\n\n```rust\npub enum BetSide {\n    Green,\n    Red,\n}\n\npub enum CloseCallPhase {\n    Open,      // Round is open for bets (first 30s of candle)\n    Settled,   // Outcome determined, payouts distributed\n    Refunded,  // All bets refunded (invalid, timeout, or force close)\n}\n\npub enum Outcome {\n    Pending,\n    Green,\n    Red,\n    Refund,\n}\n```\n\n**Bet Entry:**\n```rust\npub struct BetEntry {\n    pub player: Pubkey,\n    pub amount_lamports: u64,\n}\n```\n\n**Global Config (PDA: `[\"closecall_config\"]`):**\n```rust\npub struct CloseCallConfig {\n    pub authority: Pubkey,\n    pub treasury: Pubkey,\n    pub pyth_feed_id: [u8; 32],          // BTC/USD feed ID\n    pub betting_window_secs: u32,         // default 30\n    pub max_entries_per_side: u8,         // default 32\n    pub paused: bool,\n    pub bump: u8,\n}\n```\n\n**Close Call Round (PDA: `[\"cc_round\", &round_id]`):**\n```rust\npub struct CloseCallRound {\n    pub round_id: [u8; 8],                // Backend-generated, used in PDA seeds\n    pub server: Pubkey,                   // Server wallet that paid rent & settles\n    pub phase: CloseCallPhase,\n\n    #[max_len(32)]\n    pub green_entries: Vec<BetEntry>,\n    #[max_len(32)]\n    pub red_entries: Vec<BetEntry>,\n    pub green_pool: u64,\n    pub red_pool: u64,\n\n    pub open_price: i64,                  // Pyth price (scaled integer)\n    pub open_price_expo: i32,             // Pyth exponent\n    pub close_price: i64,                 // 0 until settled\n\n    pub created_at: i64,                  // Unix timestamp\n    pub betting_ends_at: i64,             // Unix timestamp\n    pub resolve_deadline: i64,            // Timeout deadline\n\n    pub outcome: Outcome,\n    pub total_fee: u64,\n    pub bump: u8,\n}\n```\n\n**Event:**\n```rust\npub struct RoundSettled {\n    pub round_id: [u8; 8],\n    pub outcome: Outcome,\n    pub open_price: i64,\n    pub close_price: i64,\n    pub green_pool: u64,\n    pub red_pool: u64,\n    pub total_fee: u64,\n    pub num_winners: u8,\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations Across All Three Files\n\n1. **Frontend uses **dollar amounts** (`PlayerBet.amount: number` is in $), on-chain uses **lamports** (`BetEntry.amount_lamports: u64`)\n2. **Frontend phase names** (betting/locked/resolving/complete) differ from **on-chain phase names** (Open/Settled/Refunded)\n3. **Frontend outcome** uses strings (green/red/doji), **on-chain outcome** is a Rust enum (Green/Red/Refund/Pending)\n4. **On-chain supports max 32 entries per side**, frontend has no documented hard limit\n5. **Pyth price is stored as i64 with exponent** on-chain; frontend interpolates prices during round progression\n6. **Config betting window: 30 seconds** on-chain, but **frontend constants show 10s** (BETTING_WINDOW_MS = 10000)\n7. **candle_progress** (0.0 to 1.0) drives price interpolation with 3-phase logic (bullish/bearish branches)"}],"totalDurationMs":29205,"totalTokens":42045,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6196,"cache_read_input_tokens":33254,"output_tokens":2590,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6196},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
